From: lundman@kauri.vuw.ac.nz (L Lundman)
Subject: Re: Network usage patches, replies
Date: 30 Nov 1993 18:50:24 GMT

In article <1993Nov30.134527.1229@sun0.urz.uni-heidelberg.de> hare@mathi.uni-heidelberg.de (Hannes Reinecke) writes:

>Do you think it's an good Idea to cut the transmission if the account runs out
>  of money ?  Would it be better to handle it sort of flexible, that the user
>  could stretch it in order to close a session correctly (e.g. a FTP session, 
>  where it would be a very bad idea to close the session during transmitting.)
>  And, you could charge the user anyway, since he has to come to the Admin if
>  he ever want Internet services again.

We thought of that first, but we were told that a) Test period for 3 months,
and we (the higher powers) are not sattisfied you are off the net and
b) You (us, running the machine) pay the traffic even if the users don't pay
you.

So we wanted to be sure users pay ahead of using their money, in the future
when we perhaps have more moolah to play with we might choose to go the cleaner
way.

Kef
